<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4636906-angie-kim"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1528905737i/4636906._UY100_CR12,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4636906-angie-kim">Angie Kim</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Not sure how fair it is for me to answer because I&apos;m the author, so of course I&apos;m going to say &quot;keep on reading!&quot; (haha). But I&apos;ve been trying to read<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Not sure how fair it is for me to answer because I'm the author, so of course I'm going to say "keep on reading!" (haha). But I've been trying to read all the reviews, good or bad, and some of the readers have said that it took them a while to get into it, especially because there are so many characters to get to know, but that the second half and the ending are what made them love it. I hope this is helpful, and I hope that readers will chime in!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
