        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2788680139" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9210010338456733635">3.5 stars. Phenomenal writing, mediocre storyline. <br/><br/>The hype, the hype, the hype - that’s what pulled me toward this book. <br/><br/>The synopsis alone didn’t appeal to me. It was the countless outstanding reviews (and the Traveling Friends who added as a group read) that enticed me to pick this up. I’m happy that I read it and I truly think it was excellent writing, especially for a debut novel. For me, the plot had a strong start that slowly fizzled out as the story progressed. It didn’t keep my curiosit</span>
  <span id="freeText9210010338456733635" style="display:none">3.5 stars. Phenomenal writing, mediocre storyline. <br /><br />The hype, the hype, the hype - that’s what pulled me toward this book. <br /><br />The synopsis alone didn’t appeal to me. It was the countless outstanding reviews (and the Traveling Friends who added as a group read) that enticed me to pick this up. I’m happy that I read it and I truly think it was excellent writing, especially for a debut novel. For me, the plot had a strong start that slowly fizzled out as the story progressed. It didn’t keep my curiosity piqued and I completely lost interest in the second half. <br /><br />This is the case of me not being the right reader for this storyline. Please take the time to read the countless raving reviews because there is a lot of love for this book. I will be interested to see what the author comes out with next as her writing was impressive and very promising. <br /><br />This was a Traveling Friends read that lead to one of our best discussions yet! I was the outlier with my feeling on this one. Please check out our blog for our reviews:<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://twosisterslostinacoulee.com/2019/07/16/miracle-creek-by-angie-kim-angiekimwriter-goodreads/">https://twosisterslostinacoulee.com/2...</a></span>
